Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @diced salami{2%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly crisp, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @tortelloni{9%ounce} to pan with salami. Cook, stirring, until tortelloni begin to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium. Carefully stir in @marinara sauce{14%ounce}, @water{1/2%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover and cook until tortelloni and sauce are warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Use 1 cup water for 4 servings.

Stir in @peas{4%ounce}. Cook, uncovered, until peas are warmed through and sauce has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes} (if sauce seems too thick, stir in additional water a splash at a time until desired consistency is reached). Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide tortelloni between #bowls{} and serve.